    "Still, the model remained stable and showed clear downward loss trajectory, indicating that further training would likely yield stronger results.",
    "This validates that DRaFT-Q can be extended not only to larger models but also more diverse datasets without additional architectural tuning.These findings highlight the promise of using lightweight, biologically inspired adaptation signals-such as rank growth and token-level rewards-to guide fine-tuning more intelligently than static heuristics.",
    "DRaFT-Q bridges the gap between efficiency and adaptability in PEFT methods, unlocking scalable and interpretable fine-tuning across tasks and model sizes.",
    "Limitations and Future WorkDespite the success of DRaFT-Q on a wide range of benchmarks, several limitations remain, most of which stem from hardware constraints and the scope of experimental evaluation.",
    "All experiments in this study were performed on a single NVIDIA T4 GPU (16GB VRAM), except for the LLaMA-2-13B run, which used L40 GPUs for limited training."
